definitions: (of the feet of a swimming bird or other aquatic animal) having the toes connected by a membrane.
shortDefinitions: (of feet of swimming bird or other aquatic animal) having toes connected by membrane

definitions: (of fingers or toes) abnormally united for all or part of their length by a fold of skin.
shortDefinitions: (of fingers or toes) abnormally united for all or part of their length by fold of skin

definitions: (of a band or strip of tough material) made from webbing or similar fabric
shortDefinitions: (of band or strip of tough material) made from webbing or similar fabric
